@ryangrim The government did play a big role in the history of Silicon Valley, but not in the way you imagine. A large percentage of early orders for microelectronics came from the government, for use in military aircraft, missiles, and the space program.

@ryangrim But the fact that SV was grown on government money in that sense doesn't mean the public has some claim on it. This was sales, not subsidy. The public already got something in return for that money: a lot of chips.

@ryangrim In fact it's an important thing for governments to remember that you can't create industries in the way you seem to be imagining. Subsidies get absorbed, producing nothing. It's much more effective to place orders for things that are hard to build.

